Tags.string 'NodeComment': We do not want the platform to tilt too much. We also avoid any Z rotation for now.

We wanted the platform to have some juciness. This might be an unusual setup but it shows the power of control rig. No skeletal mesh is involved. We created the two bones "anchor" and "platform". 
The platform has a slight Z offset to the anchor and is parented. 
Then we use some math and mainly the verlet simulation node to introduce a drag and a rotation of the platform depending on the anchor movement. With the control rig component in the BP_platform the calculated location and rotation is used to move the platform mesh.
project location and direction downwards, use the verlet on the location and calculate a rotation from that which add to the platforms existing rotation
Use a function for a cleaner setup that clamps the rotation so the platform do not rotate around Z and has hard limits how ffar it can tilt.
Use a verlet to have a bit of a drag. Especially when the platform turns direction this helps.
